Clam Dip

- 8oz brand-name cream cheese
Soften at room temperature until easily handled.

- 6.5 oz canned minced clams
Drain clams, reserving juice

In a small bowl, mix 1/4 cup of reserved clam juice with cream cheese.
Mash together until creamy

- 1 Tbsp lemon juice
- 1 tsp worcestershire sauce
- 1/2 tsp salt
- 1/4 tsp monosodium glutamate
- 1/8 tsp garlic salt
- 1/8 tsp pepper
Combine clams and cream cheese mixture with the rest of the ingredients, and mix together well.

Cover with plastic wrap and allow to chill in fridge for at least 30 minutes.
